File: Amplats posted an increase in earnings. AFP JOHANNESBURG - The world's largest platinum miner, Anglo American Platinum, has reported bumper profits driven by surging metal prices and higher output. In the six months ended December 2021, the miner reported a more than double profit. It benefited from higher prices and refined production, which boosted sales volumes. READ: Amplats expects up to 70% profit surge The miner's net profit for the year was R78.98-billion compared with R30.34-billion a year earlier. The company says it expects the market balance for PGMs to tighten this year with improving demand, as production of light-duty vehicles increases. The group has declared a dividend of R125 per share.